  "local_port": 58936,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Account opening in Zerodha states 48 hours, I have submitted all documents and it has been 10 days with no luck. Pathetic support, how to escalate?",
  "response": "If you've been waiting for 10 days to open your Zerodha account and have not received any updates, you can try the following steps to escalate the issue:\n\n1. **Contact Customer Support**: Reach out to Zerodha customer support directly. Provide them with your application details and any reference number you might have received. You can contact them via:\n   - Phone: Call their support team at the number available on the official Zerodha website.\n   - Email: Send an email detailing your issue to their official support email address.\n   - Chat Support: If available, use their online chat support for quicker assistance.\n\n2. **Social Media**: Sometimes companies respond quicker via social media platforms. Tweet about your issue tagging Zerodha's official Twitter handle or post on their Facebook page. Be clear and concise about your problem.\n\n3. **Raise a Ticket**: Visit their support portal at [Zerodha Support](https://support.zerodha.com/). Look for an option to raise a ticket or submit a request with your account opening details.\n\n4. **Visit an Office**: If feasible, visit the nearest Zerodha office or franchise for direct assistance.\n\n5. **SEBI Complaint**: If none of the above steps work, as a last resort, you can file a complaint with SEBI (Securities and Exchange Board of India) against Zerodha using the SCORES platform. However, this should be considered only after all direct communication attempts with Zerodha have failed.\n\nRemember to keep a record of all your communications for reference during the resolution process.",
